</p>

<p>
<h3>Version 1.1, February 2nd 2007</h3>

<b>Changes</b>

<ul>
<li> ADD: Added blank password check and password request dialog when opening remote files or trying to connect the terminal (should now only need to open the Options/Network page to change the username and hostname)</li>
<li> ADD: Added indefinite progress dialog to show something's happening during long network operations</li>
<li> ADD: Added ability to look at remote directories outside $HOME</li>
<li> ADD: Resizing the terminal window now informs the server of the resize</li>
<li> ADD: Line number printing is now optional</li>
<li> ADD: File icons in the RemoteFileDialog are now pulled directly from the user's system </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li> CHG: Resizing the window now makes the terminal resize itself proportionally</li>
<li> CHG: SSH key caching has been improved</li>
<li> CHG: Removed references to MinGW (commented out until local compiling is added)</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li> FIX: Disabled "Can't add image to imagelist" message while loading file icons</li>
<li> FIX: Fixed problem with debugging filenames that have an underscore</li>
<li> FIX: Fixed crash while loading non-source files (and disabled syntax highlighting for those files as well)</li>
<li> FIX: Fixed annoying repetitive "first chance exception" error caused by updating a non-existent toolbar</li>
<li> FIX: Fixed erratic terminal focus problems</li>
<li> FIX: Fixed crash caused that occurred when editing a previous commandline</li>
<li> FIX: Fixed problem when trying to view a directory the user doesn't have access to</li>

</ul>

<b>Known Bugs</b>
<ul>
<li>Print preview is still rather funky.</li>
</ul>

</p>

<br />

<p>
<h3>Version 1.0, April 26 2004</h3>


